The '''Ministry of Education''' ('''MOE''' or '''MoE'''; {{Lang-ms|Kementerian Pendidikan}}) is a cabinet-level [[Ministries of Brunei|ministry]] in the [[Government of Brunei]] which oversees education in [[Brunei]]. The head of the ministry is the Minister of Education and the incumbent is Hamzah Sulaiman.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://borneobulletin.com.bn/sultan-reshuffles-cabinet/|title=Sultan reshuffles Cabinet {{!}} Borneo Bulletin Online|website=borneobulletin.com.bn|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.moe.gov.bn/SitePages/Organizational%20Chart.aspx|title=Ministry of Education, Brunei Darussalam|website=www.moe.gov.bn|language=en-SG|access-date=2018-02-12}}</ref>
== Budget == For the fiscal year of 2018-19, the Ministry of Education has been allocated with an annual budget of [[Brunei dollar|B$]]696 million ([[United States dollar|US$]]530 million as of March 2018)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://xe.com/currencyconverter/convert/?Amount=696000000&From=BND&To=USD|title=XE: Convert BND/USD. Brunei Darussalam Dollar to United States Dollar|website=xe.com|language=en|access-date=2018-03-21}}</ref>, an increase of about B$30 million from the previous year.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://thescoop.co/2018/03/21/14th-legco-session-ends-budget-passed/|title=14th LegCo session ends with $5.3B budget passed - The Scoop|date=2018-03-21|work=The Scoop|access-date=2018-03-21|language=en-GB}}</ref> It has the third largest budget allocation in the current fiscal year among the government ministries, after the Ministries of [[Ministry of Development (Brunei)|Development]] and [[Ministry of Finance (Brunei)|Finance]].<ref name=":0" />
