'''Piotr Feliks''' (June 11, 1883 in [[Bierówka]] near [[Jasło]] &ndash; August 3 or 12, 1941) was a [[Poland|Polish]] political, social and education activist.

He was imprisoned and murdered during the [[Second World War]] at [[Auschwitz concentration camp]].

